<div id="landing" class="clusterduck">
	<div class="banner">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-12">
					<h1>Clusterduck <span>Details</span></h1>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<canvas class="background"></canvas>
	</div>
	<div class="section duckintro">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 content">
					<h2>A Mobile Ad-Hoc Internet</h2>
					<p>The Clusterduck network is made up of "Ducks", small WiFi-enabled IoT devices in a 3D printed enclosure.  A single Ducklink device can connect through WiFi to consumer electronics such as a phone or a laptop.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
					<img class="block" src="/assets/clusterduck_photo01.jpg" />
					<p><em>Ducklink Casing</em></p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-5">
					<img class="block" src="/assets/clusterduck_photo03.jpg" />
					<p><em>Ducklink Casing with Exposed Electronics</em></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="section access">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 content">
					<h2>Accessing the Network</h2>
					<p>Find the network as a WiFi network on your smartphone or laptop.  A web page will pop-up automatically providing an opportunity to send information to first responders.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 content">
					<img class="gif" src="/assets/cluster_demo_vector.gif" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="section charts">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 content">
					<h2>The Ducklink</h2>
					<p>A Ducklink is the base hardware unit of a Clusterduck network. One Ducklink is an IoT WiFi device that wirelessly connects to consumer electronics.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
					<h4>WiFi Ducklink Range: 0.2 mi<sup>2</sup></h4>
					<img class="chart" src="/assets/clusterduck_cost_effectiveness_01.png" />
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
					<h4>5 Ducklinks Cover 1.00 mi<sup>2</sup></h4>
					<img class="chart" src="/assets/clusterduck_cost_effectiveness_02.png" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="section charts">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 content">
					<h2>The Mamaduck</h2>
					<p>The Mamaduck is the central hub of the Clusterduck network. A single Mamaduck is an IoT LoRa device that connects to Ducklinks over long range.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
					<h4>Mamaduck Range:  3.1 mi<sup>2</sup></h4>
					<img class="chart mamarange" src="/assets/clusterduck_cost_effectiveness_04.png" />
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-0">
					<h4>Mamaduck Services 5 Ducklinks</h4>
					<img class="chart" src="/assets/clusterduck_cost_effectiveness_03.png" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="section charts">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 content">
					<h2>The Clusterduck</h2>
					<p>The Clusterduck is the complete network generated by a Mamaduck and her Ducklinks.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-1">
					<h4>One Clusterduck covers 1.20 mi<sup>2</sup></h4>
					<img class="chart" src="/assets/clusterduck_cost_effectiveness_05.png" />
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-offset-0">
					<h4>5 Clusterducks Cover 6.00 mi<sup>2</sup></h4>
					<img class="chart" src="/assets/clusterduck_cost_effectiveness_06.png" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<%= render 'layouts/footer' %>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
	
	$(".legend .link").on("click", function() {

		if ($(this).hasClass("cost")) {
			$(".product-roadmap").fadeOut("fast")
			setTimeout(function() {
				$(".cost-effectiveness").fadeIn("fast")
			}, 200)
		} else if ($(this).hasClass("roadmap")) {
			$(".cost-effectiveness").fadeOut("fast")
			setTimeout(function() {
				$(".product-roadmap").fadeIn("fast")
			}, 200)
		}
	})

</script>

<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/particlesjs/2.2.2/particles.min.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">

	function initParticles(x) {
	    if (x.matches) { // If media query matches
			var particles = Particles.init({
				selector: '.background',
			  	color: '#292929',
			  	connectParticles: true,
			  	sizeVariations: 5,
			  	maxParticles: 20,
			  	speed: .3
			});
	    } else {
			var particles = Particles.init({
				selector: '.background',
			  	color: '#292929',
			  	connectParticles: true,
			  	sizeVariations: 5,
			  	maxParticles: 150,
			  	speed: .3
			});
	    }
	}

	
	
	$(window).load(function() {
		var x = window.matchMedia("(max-width: 768px)")
		initParticles(x) // Call listener function at run time
		x.addListener(initParticles) // Attach listener function on state changes
	});
	
</script>